REPORT ON AT&T via NewsNet
JANUARY 1, 1996

NETWORK SYSTEMS ACQUIRES PHILIPS' EUROPEAN PUBLIC NETWORK ASSETS

AT&T Network Systems recently signed the final purchase
agreement with Philips Electronics N.V. whereby AT&T will
acquire a portion of the public network assets held by Philips'
Communications Services Division.  Network Systems bought the
assets related to four Philips units:  Cellular Infrastructure,
Managed Transport Networks, Microwave Transmission and Access
and Transmission.

Financial terms and conditions were not disclosed.




