REPORT ON AT&T via NewsNet
JANUARY 1, 1996

AT&T BEGINS LOCAL PUSH IN NEW JERSEY, MARYLAND AND GEORGIA

AT&T filed an application with New Jersey regulators recently,
asking for the green light to offer local service to consumers
and businesses in that state.  The New Jersey Board of Public
Utilities last month began discussing opening the market for
local service.  AT&T, in the filing, outlined the general terms
and conditions under which the carrier plans to offer local
service in the Garden State, including reselling services from
the incumbent RBOC, Bell Atlantic.

The petition also called for number portability and intraLATA
presubscription in local competition.  The New Jersey request
comes at the same time as similar petitions in Maryland and
Georgia.




