<A NAME = "10"></A>Copyright
REPORT ON AT&T via NewsNet
JANUARY 1, 1996

MCI TO PROVIDE BUSINESS SERVICE IN EASTERN EUROPE, BALTIC STATES

MCI announced recently it will provide private line service to
multinational companies in the United States doing business in
the Newly Independent States (NIS), including Russia and the
Baltics.

The Skyline Direct Satellite Service includes everything from
design, installation of the Very Small Aperture Terminal (VSAT)
antenna and system maintenance for companies that need
international private lines from 64 kilobits/second up to 2
megabits/ second.  The system can accommodate voice, data, fax
and video, either independently or in combination.




