REPORT ON AT&T via NewsNet
JANUARY 1, 1996

MCI OFFERS CUSTOMERS TIPS TO PREVENT COMPUTER FRAUD

MCI officials said that to help prevent hackers from
compromising networks, businesses should make sure that their
systems sit behind firewalls, change passwords frequently and
use a "call-back" procedure to verify distribution of any
sensitive information over the phone.




