FRANCE TELECOM JOINS INTERNET

France Telecom will from March 15 provide access to the Internet from
anywhere in France for the price of a local call.  As well as Internet
access it will also provide its own services on the Internet through
its France Telecom Multi Media subsidiary.

At the same time, France Telecom is also proposing to cut the cost of
its Minitel on-line service and to increase the speed of the service as
well.





