OFTEL'S FAIR TRADING PROPOSALS

The regulator last month published for consultation its controversial
proposed licence amendment on anti-competitive practice (Telecom
Markets, 283/14).  BT immediately expressed ``disappointment'' that
Oftel was determined to adopt what it called ``sweeping new powers''.

BT has until March, when the consultation period is due to end, to
decide whether to accept the licence amendment.  If it does not, Oftel
will refer the issue to the Monopolies and Mergers Commission.





