January 18, 1996

SHOPPING BY PHONE

Supermarket chain Sainsbury is introducing a home-shopping service
whereby armchair customers select produce from a catalogue and dial a
special number quoting a four-figure code for each product.  The goods
are then delivered to the customer's home.





