January 8, 1996

AMERITECH PAYMENT CENTERS

          Ameritech Corp. will close its 28 remaining company-owned
customer payment centers in five states and double the number of
"mechanized agents," such as banks and convenience stores, at
which customers can pay telephone bills.  

          According to a company spokesman, only a "handful" of
employees will be affected by the closings, and most will be
reassigned within the company. 



