Satellite Services:
Globalstar Stake Cut

     New York-based investment firm Cumberland Associates has cut
its stake in Globalstar Telecommunications Ltd., the public equity
portion of Globalstar L.P., to 6.2%.  It now owns 621,400 shares of
Globalstar, according to a Schedule 13D amendment filed with the
Securities and Exchange Commission Jan. 11.  

     Cumberland Associates said it sold 115,000 shares between Nov.
17, 1995, and Dec. 22, 1995, at prices ranging from $25.90 to
$36.00 per share.  

     The firm purchased 5,000 shares on Nov. 27, 1995, at $24.81
per share.  Schedule 13D filings are required of "aggressive"
institutional investors who own more than 5% of a particular issue.



