Survey of the Americas:
Unitel Restructuring

     Interexchange carrier Unitel Communications, Inc., of Canada
has completed its ownership restructuring.  Under the new
structure, the voting shares of the holding company, Unitel
Communications Holdings, Inc., will be held by AT&T Canada (33%),
The Bank of Nova Scotia (28%), The Toronto-Dominion Bank (23%), and
The Royal Bank of Canada (16%). 

     Unitel said the arrangement is "in full compliance with the
limitation on foreign ownership and control permitted under
Canadian law."  The new shareholders have agreed to invest $250
million in Unitel.



