Emerging Services:
DBS Auction Hearing

     The U.S. Court of Appeals in Washington is scheduled to hear
oral arguments March 18 on Advanced Communications Corp.'s appeal
of the FCC order revoking its direct broadcast satellite (DBS)
authority (case no. 95-1561).  Primestar Partners L.P. and Tempo
DBS, Inc., are included in the consolidated appeal.  

     CTA, Inc., of Rockville, Md., asked the court to issue a stay
barring the FCC from proceeding with a Jan. 24 auction of two
construction permits for building and operating a direct broadcast
satellite (DBS) system.  



